# Project Conventions

**Follow existing project conventions exactly.** Before writing new code, read nearby files that solve a similar problem and mirror how they do it.

Stack: **TanStack Start** (SSR), **TanStack Router** (file-based), **React 19**, **TypeScript** (strict), **Vite**, **Tailwind CSS v4**, **shadcn/ui** (radix-lyra), **lucide-react**, **Bun**.

## Layout

| Area | Location |
|------|----------|
| Routes | `src/routes/` — one file per route, export `Route` from `createFileRoute` |
| UI primitives | `src/components/ui/` — shadcn components |
| App components | `src/components/` |
| Utilities | `src/lib/` |
| Hooks | `src/hooks/` |
| Global styles / theme | `src/styles.css` |
| Path alias | `@/*` → `src/*` |

Do not edit `src/routeTree.gen.ts` — it is generated by the router plugin.

## Integration points

- **New pages** — add a file under `src/routes/` using `createFileRoute`; follow `index.tsx` and `__root.tsx` patterns.
- **Navigation** — use TanStack Router (`Link`, `useNavigate`, loaders/actions). Don't bolt on a second router.
- **UI primitives** — prefer `npx shadcn@latest add <component>` or match existing `src/components/ui/` patterns (CVA variants, `cn()`, Radix primitives, `asChild`).
- **Styling** — Tailwind utility classes merged with `cn()` from `@/lib/utils`. Use theme tokens from `styles.css` (`bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `text-success`, `text-warning`, `text-error`, etc.) — not raw Tailwind `neutral-*` scales or one-off hex colors. Chart series colors live in `--chart-1` … `--chart-12`; read them via `getChartColors()` / `readCssVar()` rather than hard-coding hex in TS.
- **Inline `style`** — avoid for colors, spacing, and typography that belong in Tailwind or theme tokens. Use `style` only when the value is computed at runtime and cannot be expressed as a static class: chart container heights, usage-bar fill widths, sidebar width CSS variables, tooltip positioning, and similar dynamic layout. Prefer CSS variables set via `style` when a token needs a runtime value.
- **Icons** — `lucide-react`, consistent sizing with sibling components.

## Component design

**Model variation with types, not branching.** When behaviour differs by kind, use discriminated unions, CVA variant props, composition, or separate components — not string flags with `switch` chains that need comments to interpret.

- **Extend existing abstractions** — route files follow the `createFileRoute` contract; UI components follow shadcn/CVA patterns.
- **Shared logic belongs up the tree** — extract a hook or shared component when multiple call sites need it; don't duplicate.
- **Only where it earns its keep** — one variant with no second implementation stays concrete. No base component for a single child.

## Surrounding context

**Read the subsystem before you write code.**

- Trace an existing route end-to-end (file route → component → imports) before adding a sibling.
- Check `__root.tsx` for shell, head meta, and global layout before changing page structure.
- No loose workarounds — don't bypass TanStack Router, shadcn patterns, or the `@/` alias with one-off hacks.
